To ease the manual workload, the wealth of data from the Copernicus Sentinel sensors  has been somewhat integrated into the CORINE mapping workflow, and has also led to the  development of Copernicus Land cover services high spatial resolution maps  (https://land.copernicus.eu/pan -european/high -resolution -layers ).
Recently,  Sentinel -2 data has  been used to create a 10m pan -European land cover/use map (S2GLC) for ca irca 2017  (http://s2glc.cbk.waw.pl/ ) (Malinowski et al., 2020) .

To address the n eed for fine -grained land cover data, the European Space Agency recently  initiated the development of the S2GLC map over Europe at 10m resolution  (http://s2glc.cbk.waw.pl/ ) (Malinowski et al., 2020) .
